Job_Description:
We are a real estate development company with a proven history of innovation and award winning design. We are recognized for our good social conscience, entrepreneurial spirit and long-sightedness. Ultimately, we are working very hard to create valuable opportunities for our employees, customers and neighbors.
Wesgroup Properties started as a family business in British Columbia more than 50 years ago and today is one of Western Canada’s largest private real estate organizations with a diversified portfolio spanning residential and commercial real estate in most asset classes. Wesgroup owns and manages over 3.5 million square feet of commercial property and has built more than 7000 homes in 100 communities.
The Financial & Legal team is looking for an experienced professional to fill the role of a Finance and Acquisitions Analyst. Whilst the role with be within the Finance and Legal team, there is overlap of information and work that will with Acquisitions & Research. The primary activities will be (1) valuation support, (2) loan application and maintenance support and (3) acquisitions support. The role of the Finance and Acquisitions Analyst will consist of, but not be limited to, the following:


Job Responsibilities:
Engage and oversee the preparation of 3rd party reports, most notably appraisals, to assist with financing applications and ongoing reporting;
Co-ordination and communication with the development, sales, marketing and construction teams informing the finance and acquisition processes;
Undertake and update market research related to property sales, new developments, including researching municipal policy and other relevant sources (i.e. Metro Vancouver Regional Growth Study, ProvBC …) that inform construction and development;
Perform various valuation methods: comparison method, direct capitalization method and DCF for the valuation of real estate for internal purposes;
Maintain current valuation in internal reporting and proforma documents;
Perform due diligence, research, analysis and documentation of transactions;
Prepare proformas and related financial analysis to evaluate the merits of investment decisions; and,
Prepare presentations summarizing the findings of due diligence and investment thesis and conviction.
Qualifications and Knowledge:
A track record of success in an analyst type role where the candidate demonstrated strong problem-solving skills in a real estate environment. Experience in real estate development is very important for this role. Proven Vancouver market knowledge and established presence within the brokerage community;
University degree in Business, Economics, Land Economics is considered an asset. Yardi and VTS experience is an asset;
Possesses a strong curiosity to learn about real estate and all of its dynamics. Strong desire to build capabilities through hard work and an open mind.
Ability to synthesize a large amount of data into a concise analysis, both quantitatively and qualitatively.
Ability to articulate strengths and weakness of a transaction to appropriately influence third party report providers.
Possesses a self-starter mentality to work with other people across many other teams and build a network.
Has experience with various software platforms related to real estate. Solid technical skills in Microsoft Office platform.
Has an understanding of planning, zoning, permitting, and servicing aspects of development to relate when and how value is being added the process.
We will provide a competitive salary and benefits package for the right candidate as well as a professional and rewarding working environment. If you are interested in this exciting opportunity please visit our website at www.wesgroup.ca/careers/ and apply with your resume and cover letter.
We thank all applicants for their interest however only those selected for follow-up will be contacted.
